DEFINITIONS

"norxs" means norxs Technology LLC, a limited liability company organised
under the laws of the State of Wyoming, United States of America.

"SOFTWARE" means the norxs Deterministic TSN Zonal Backbone — a
production-grade AUTOSAR C++14 IEEE TSN stack implementing IEEE 802.1Qbv
gate control scheduling, IEEE 802.1AS-Rev gPTP synchronisation, IEEE 802.1CB
frame replication and elimination, IEEE 802.1Qci per-stream filtering and
policing, and IEEE 802.1AE MACsec line-rate encryption, targeting NXP i.MX8X
SoC with SJA1110 / Marvell 88Q5050 switch ASICs, as published at
https://github.com/norxs-tech/tsn-zonal-backbone, together with all
associated documentation, test suites, and build system files.

"PERMITTED USE" means reading, studying, evaluating, and building upon the
SOFTWARE for the sole purpose of assessing the technical capabilities of
norxs Technology LLC, conducting internal proof-of-concept evaluation, or
academic research with appropriate attribution.

"COMMERCIAL USE" means any use of the SOFTWARE, in whole or in part, in a
product, service, or system that is sold, licensed, or otherwise transferred
to a third party, or that generates direct or indirect revenue, including but
not limited to integration into automotive ECUs, PDUs, network switches,
simulation tools, AUTOSAR stacks, or safety-critical systems.

